Set Up Permissions for the Google Cloud Storage Connector

Create interoperability keys in the Google Cloud Storage (GCS) service to enable interoperability between GCS and Amazon S3. Interoperability keys are also called HMAC (Hash-based Message Authentication Code) keys and are used for GCS data ingestion and extraction.

NOTE These steps involve third-party products so we can’t guarantee the accuracy of the steps involving Google Cloud Console.
Create Interoperability Keys for Google Cloud Storage Bucket
Interoperability keys, also called HMAC (Hash-based Message Authentication Code) keys, are credentials that you associate with a Google Cloud service or user account. We recommend using a Google Cloud service account with HMAC keys for production workloads.
Set Permissions for Google Cloud Storage Bucket
Set up permissions on your Google Cloud Storage bucket.
Add a Principal to Google Cloud Storage Bucket
Add a service account as principal to your Google Cloud Storage bucket.
Validate Google Cloud Connector Bucket Credentials
A successful creation of Google Cloud Storage (GCS) connector indicates that the credentials supplied are valid. If there's an issue we suggest you to validate the credentials using a Python script.
